<subSubSection id="7502BA1EEC083E3E95BB9DD9C8D0CE87" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="DC23DA93036D19C422C791798FBF61A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77A76805BB392A06966DC04CD8236F7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ABB206ABD6D3872975A18CA7A80C104A" genus="B." lsidName="B. hahiepiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="hahiepiana">
<emphasis id="2B04D135CB8EB080BF02F518976C826B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. hahiepiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H.Q. Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt in broadly ovate asymmetric leaves with slightly truncate or round apex and the corned berry fruit, but different from it in the broadly ovate or rotund leaves (vs. ovate), almost flat adaxial surface of leaves (vs. puckered), glabrous outer surface of petals (vs. with red trichomes), 4-loculed and glabrous berry fruit covered by dense white spots (vs. 3-loculed and pubescent fruit covered by the lax white spots).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
