<subSubSection id="9A19410F3F527F1333E7C7F5FED8AC30" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="notes">
<paragraph id="35A85BB817EF1B4C3C61098C774DC62A" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="424153FDB770F4F2973312EE9F2A03D3" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Currently six species from 
<taxonomicName id="BC5123A5D56B04B2EF1A9898169CF811" authority="Sphenanthera" genus="B." lsidName="subsp. section" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="section" section="Sphenanthera" species="hahiepiana" subSpecies="section">section Sphenanthera</taxonomicName>
are recognised as occurring in Vietnam: 
<taxonomicName id="2BD51FAABF4E1CC848C03975F9CC0C27" authorityName="Craib" authorityYear="1912" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia acetosella" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis id="2096C6389DDC4C4138B5A37224EC3EB0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Begonia acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib, 
<taxonomicName id="963923EB6B0C023433B3BD085712B3E2" genus="B." lsidName="B. balansana" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="balansana">
<emphasis id="6172363E09D6C4F0CB2EB3CF5905E8AB" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. balansana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gagnep., 
<taxonomicName id="76315F122C79546652E654E235ADB6D8" genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis id="02FF0CA672A63453A661A6DB31D3E449" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Irmscher, 
<taxonomicName id="3B3215F5C223FD27C2D6BB825034D98E" genus="B." lsidName="B. longifolia" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="longifolia">
<emphasis id="16611C8A73B6A829B211BC8B116E5EAA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. longifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Blume, 
<taxonomicName id="2D22825CAD527575465CF5BFAABB55F2" genus="B." lsidName="B. ceratocarpa" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="ceratocarpa">
<emphasis id="E72DDB0D6E50923B528CF816818BDAC1" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. ceratocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S.H. Huang &amp; Y.M. Shui and 
<taxonomicName id="110EDED2B3087F5D447B1136E1F518D7" genus="B." lsidName="B. hahiepiana" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="hahiepiana">
<emphasis id="C3D723E83462C8ED06436329885A618E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. hahiepiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H.Q. Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt. Although this new species grows together with 
<taxonomicName id="0ED91F6A0607D4D417385FABB357446D" genus="B." lsidName="B. hahiepiana" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="hahiepiana">
<emphasis id="E7260AF43C41DCE234582E0616705759" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. hahiepiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is easily distinguished by the glabrous and 4-loculed berry fruit, which has been discussed in the above diagnostic description. Within the Vietnamese species of the section, the stemless habit, the narrow inflorescence and the small horned appendage of the berry fruit indicate that the new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="57EED78B99D44B932B69AF7F3E3777BD" authorityName="S. H. Huang &amp; Y. M. Shui" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia ceratocarpa" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ceratocarpa">
<emphasis id="02A33AB0DD69438EAC322CB60DA075EA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Begonia ceratocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0EF3CCB81EB1EDED7184010E7DF05B22" genus="B." lsidName="B. balansana" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="balansana">
<emphasis id="EA115FD11640D6D4560E313060E36BC7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. balansana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The detailed comparison reveals that it is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F07BB65D26AA88AE9F7639247D03F1BF" genus="B." lsidName="B. ceratocarpa" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="ceratocarpa">
<emphasis id="DFD721C75AD9299E9492C282CD38A068" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. ceratocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 3-4-loculed fruits than 
<taxonomicName id="3CB9AA97F38C2DF2C374505DC13C3003" genus="B." lsidName="B. balansana" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="balansana">
<emphasis id="027A284AECB2317AD75FB0FDAB879D76" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. balansana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 6-7-loculed fruit. It is different from 
<taxonomicName id="622EB7FF6DF12CFDA7CB7F9670CF5718" genus="B." lsidName="B. ceratocarpa" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="ceratocarpa">
<emphasis id="5B09ADE23B7CC531DEA2075F5B809D04" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">B. ceratocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the broadly ovate or rotund leaves (
<emphasis id="0C931F74CED970632FA6D8FAC781BCC7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
ovate), the unlobed leaf blade (
<emphasis id="E9612C71C53BFF1D87B2E955B07E9563" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
slightly lobed), round leaf top (
<emphasis id="6134D4C73CAC15EDAD2DC1487F5525E7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
acuminate leaf top), petioles with red pubes (
<emphasis id="99A2D5736D7118D7F7F363493B0DB87A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
with brown 1anes), 5 female tepals (
<emphasis id="249548C6391E1C1E3A686CE381755652" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
3), densely white-spotted surface of berry fruit (
<emphasis id="218B08DC3899A979951F4033BAB96BFF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
sparely spotted), truncate fruit top without a beak (
<emphasis id="0F43394EE216656B66D8D03C14C4233D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">vs.</emphasis>
an acute fruit top with a beak).
</paragraph>
